      @Deprecated public Builder(android.content.Context context, String orgId, String fpServer)
      Deprecated.
      Pass the mandatory params for ThreatMetrix signal group configuration here.
      Parameters:
      context - application context
      orgId - Unique orgId assigned to each organisation by ThreatMetrix
      fpServer - Fingerprint server to use. Note this is a domain and not a URL. Pass value as h-sdk.online-metrix.net for this version. This value may be changed in future. This API will be removed in future versions, use alternate constructor instead.
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setPackageScanTimeLimit

      public GAHTMXConfig.Builder setPackageScanTimeLimit(int packageScanTimeLimit, TimeUnit timeUnit)
      Sets the maximum time to spend to process packages during init(). 0 disables the limit NOTE: that the limit isn't precise, the logic is simply: if(timeSpent < packageScanTimeLimit) processNextPackage(); So the time taken can be in the region of timeLimit + time take to process last package.
      Parameters:
      packageScanTimeLimit - in TimeUnit
      timeUnit - TimeUnit for package Scan TimeLimit
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setScreenOffTimeout

      public GAHTMXConfig.Builder setScreenOffTimeout(int screenOffTimeout, TimeUnit timeUnit)
      Sets the screen off timeout (in seconds). By setting this argument when the screen is off future profiling will be blocked after screenOffTimeout seconds. Any profiling done after that will return instantly with the result of TMXStatusCode.TMX_Blocked. Profiling will be enabled when the screen turns back on.
      Parameters:
      screenOffTimeout - Number of the TimeUnit before disabling profiling after screen goes off. The Default value is 180 seconds (3 minutes) and valid interval is between 1 and 1800 seconds (30 minutes).
      timeUnit - time unit for screenOffTimeout.
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setSessionIDTimeout

      @Deprecated public GAHTMXConfig.Builder setSessionIDTimeout(int timeoutSec)
      Deprecated.
      API to set cache timeout value for ThreatMetrix sessionID. Once this time is passed, new profiling request will be made to ThreatMetrix SDK during next call to requestVisitID() or startPrefetchSignals(). Default value is 300 seconds. This API is deprecated and will be removed in future versions, use setSignalCacheTimeout() present in GemaltoSignalConfig instead. Timeout value passed here will be overridden by setSignalCacheTimeout() in v2.1.0 onwards and hence pass the required timeout value to the API in GemaltoSignalConfig.
      Parameters:
      timeoutSec - SessionID timeout value in seconds
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0

    • setProfileRequestTimeout

      @Deprecated public GAHTMXConfig.Builder setProfileRequestTimeout(int timeoutSec)
      Deprecated.
      Timeout value in seconds to prefetch and cache the sessionID value in GAH SDK. If profiling is not completed within this time, no session ID signal will be considered during next call to requestVisitID(). Default value is 5seconds This API is deprecated and will be removed in future versions, use setSignalPrefetchTimeout() present in GemaltoSignalConfig instead. Timeout value passed here will be overridden by setSignalPrefetchTime() in v2.1.0 onwards and hence pass the required timeout value to the API in GemaltoSignalConfig.
      Parameters:
      timeoutSec - Timeout value in seconds
      Returns:
      Config builder object
      Since:
      2.0.0
